{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KXyvEJsDHkZJVE4xS8JrCU","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 16-3: Update Proof Validation for New Tiers\n     2→<!-- verification-tier: test-provable -->\n     3→\n     4→## Status: review\n     5→\n     6→## Story\n     7→\n     8→As a codeharness developer,\n     9→I want proof validation to recognize all four verification tier names and apply enforcement rules per tier,\n    10→So that `test-provable` and `runtime-provable` stories skip Docker enforcement while `environment-provable` stories require Docker evidence.\n    11→\n    12→## Acceptance Criteria\n    13→\n    14→- [x] AC1: Given a proof with `**Tier:** test-provable`, when `validateProofQuality()` runs, then `blackBoxPass` is `true` (Docker enforcement skipped) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→- [x] AC2: Given a proof with `**Tier:** runtime-provable`, when `validateProofQuality()` runs, then `blackBoxPass` is `true` (Docker enforcement skipped) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→- [x] AC3: Given a proof with `**Tier:** environment-provable`, when `validateProofQuality()` runs, then Docker enforcement runs normally (requires `docker exec` evidence per AC) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→- [x] AC4: Given a proof with `**Tier:** escalate`, when `validateProofQuality()` runs, then `blackBoxPass` is `true` (enforcement skipped — human judgment needed) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→- [x] AC5: Given a proof with the old `**Tier:** unit-testable`, when `validateProofQuality()` runs, then it still skips Docker enforcement (backward compat) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19→- [x] AC6: Given a proof with `**Tier:** black-box`, when `validateProofQuality()` runs, then Docker enforcement runs (backward compat for old default) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20→\n    21→## Technical Notes\n    22→\n    23→**File:** `src/modules/verify/proof.ts`\n    24→\n    25→**Line 116:** The current regex is:\n    26→```typescript\n    27→const bbTierMatch = /\\*\\*Tier:\\*\\*\\s*(unit-testable|black-box)/i.exec(content);\n    28→const bbIsUnitTestable = bbTierMatch ? bbTierMatch[1].toLowerCase() === 'unit-testable' : false;\n    29→```\n    30→\n    31→Replace with:\n    32→```typescript\n    33→const bbTierMatch = /\\*\\*Tier:\\*\\*\\s*(test-provable|runtime-provable|environment-provable|escalate|unit-testable|black-box)/i.exec(content);\n    34→const tierValue = bbTierMatch ? bbTierMatch[1].toLowerCase() : null;\n    35→// Skip Docker enforcement for tiers that don't need Docker\n    36→const skipDockerEnforcement = tierValue === 'test-provable'\n    37→  || tierValue === 'runtime-provable'\n    38→  || tierValue === 'escalate'\n    39→  || tierValue === 'unit-testable'; // backward compat\n    40→```\n    41→\n    42→Then use `skipDockerEnforcement` instead of `bbIsUnitTestable` in the ternary on L118-L119.\n    43→\n    44→The logic: only `environment-provable` (and old `black-box`) require Docker evidence. Everything else skips Docker enforcement.\n    45→\n    46→## Files to Change\n    47→\n    48→- `src/modules/verify/proof.ts` — Update `**Tier:**` regex (L116) to recognize all four new tier names plus old names. Change skip logic: `test-provable`, `runtime-provable`, `escalate`, and legacy `unit-testable` all skip Docker enforcement. Only `environment-provable` and legacy `black-box` require it.\n    49→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01FBYb3WSC17Tg6VaiRjwb3D","session_id":"43e58b5f-4801-4d1c-b71e-1cb2980b19a0","uuid":"d66ee22d-01f9-477a-bfac-d19452ffe50f","timestamp":"2026-03-27T11:09:36.942Z"}
