{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FBYb3WSC17Tg6VaiRjwb3D","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**Review complete.** Here is what was done:\n\n### Fixes applied\n\n**Files changed:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/verify/proof.ts` — Refactored tier matching to use `TIER_HIERARCHY` and `LEGACY_TIER_MAP` from `types.ts` instead of hardcoded strings. Changed metrics to always be computed (not zeroed) when Docker enforcement is skipped. Only `blackBoxPass` is overridden.\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/verify/types.ts` — Added `'black-box': 'environment-provable'` to `LEGACY_TIER_MAP`.\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/verify/__tests__/verify-blackbox.test.ts` — Added 2 new tests: unrecognized tier defaults to Docker enforcement; skipped tiers still report metrics.\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/verify/__tests__/verification-tier.test.ts` — Updated count assertion from 3 to 4; added test for `black-box` mapping.\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/16-3-update-proof-validation-for-tiers.md` — Status changed to `verifying`.\n\n### Results\n- 3887 tests pass (149 files)\n- 96.86% overall coverage\n- All 158 files above 80% per-file floor\n\n## Session Issues\n\n### Bugs found\n- **HIGH** — Metrics zeroed when Docker enforcement skipped: `grepSrcCount`, `dockerExecCount`, `observabilityCount`, `otherCount` were all set to 0 instead of being computed when `skipDockerEnforcement` was true. Downstream consumers (dashboards, audit tools) would see false zeroes. **Fixed.**\n- **HIGH** — `black-box` missing from `LEGACY_TIER_MAP`: The legacy tier `black-box` was recognized in the regex but had no canonical mapping in `LEGACY_TIER_MAP`, creating an inconsistency between `types.ts` (source of truth) and `proof.ts`. **Fixed.**\n- **MEDIUM** — Hardcoded tier names in regex: The regex string literal duplicated tier names already defined in `TIER_HIERARCHY` and `LEGACY_TIER_MAP`. Adding a new tier to `types.ts` would not propagate to `proof.ts`. **Fixed** (regex now built dynamically).\n- **MEDIUM** — Skip logic duplicated tier knowledge: `skipDockerEnforcement` hardcoded which tiers skip Docker instead of deriving from normalized tier value. **Fixed** (now only `environment-provable` requires Docker; all else skips).\n- **MEDIUM** — No test for unrecognized tier value. **Fixed** (added test).\n\n### Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW)\n- The `checkBlackBoxEnforcement` function is always called now, even for `test-provable` tiers where the metrics are purely informational. Minor performance cost but needed for correctness of metrics.\n- The `validation-ac-data.ts` description at ID 72 still references \"unit-testable stories\" — stale description given the new tier system. Not blocking.\n\n### Coverage gaps\n- None. All 158 files above 80% floor. 96.86% overall.\n\n### Architecture concerns\n- The `proof.ts` module does not import or use the `VerificationTier` type for runtime validation — it relies on string comparison after regex extraction. The type is only used for the `normalizedTier` variable annotation. This is acceptable since the regex is built from the canonical sources.\n\n### Items sent back for re-development\n- None.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 21\n- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 6, Edit: 5, Grep: 5, Glob: 4, Skill: 1, Write: 0\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): full test suite run #1 (~30 lines), full test suite run #2 (~15 lines), blackbox test run (~40 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 9 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: none significant — the two full test suite runs were necessary (first caught a regression, second verified the fix)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ab0e0749e0121848c (use SendMessage with to: 'ab0e0749e0121848c' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens